
[1]singe

   SINGE, v.t. sinj. To burn slightly or superficially; to burn the
   surface of a thing as the nap of cloth, or the hair of the skin; as, to
   singe off the beard. Thus riding on his curls, he seem'd to pass A
   rolling fire along, and singe the grass.

   SINGE, n. A burning of the surface; a slight burn.
